0
00:00:06.030 --> 00:00:09.709
Dear parents, if you notice
that your child has difficulty

1
00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:14.809
sitting still, is irritated
by clothing, often fidgets,

2
00:00:14.820 --> 00:00:18.868
or becomes overloaded quickly,
this may be related to an

3
00:00:18.880 --> 00:00:20.959
unintegrated galant reflex.

4
00:00:21.800 --> 00:00:24.909
This is one of the basic
reflexes that affects how a

5
00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:28.899
child feels their body and how
calmly they can remain still.

6
00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:33.609
In all the exercises in this
lesson, we will be doing

7
00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:37.409
smooth, rhythmic movements
because they are what help

8
00:00:37.420 --> 00:00:41.169
the nervous system reduce
tension and gradually

9
00:00:41.180 --> 00:00:42.639
close this reflex.

10
00:00:43.440 --> 00:00:46.549
In the case of the galant
reflex, we need to close

11
00:00:46.560 --> 00:00:50.369
it because under normal
development, this reflex

12
00:00:50.380 --> 00:00:51.859
should go away on its own.

13
00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:54.999
However, sometimes a child
needs help with that.

14
00:00:55.310 --> 00:00:57.859
That's exactly what we'll
be working on today.

15
00:00:58.340 --> 00:01:02.049
Remember that all the
exercises are very gentle,

16
00:01:02.060 --> 00:01:05.428
and here it is not speed
that matters, but quality

17
00:01:05.440 --> 00:01:06.779
and body awareness.

18
00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:10.039
Let's go through them together
and see how to do them.

19
00:01:11.960 --> 00:01:15.239
The child lies on their
back on a flat surface.

20
00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:18.259
Give the child time
to get comfortable.

21
00:01:19.130 --> 00:01:21.288
The legs are stretched
out straight,

22
00:01:21.300 --> 00:01:22.759
shoulder-width apart.

23
00:01:22.770 --> 00:01:25.559
The arms are along the body,
and the head is straight.

24
00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:29.928
On the inhale, the child
spreads their legs while the

25
00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:34.069
arms rise up, then holds this
position for two seconds.

26
00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:37.469
On the exhale, the
legs come together, and

27
00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:39.479
the arms lower down.

28
00:01:39.520 --> 00:01:42.599
The arms and legs should
work synchronously.

29
00:01:42.610 --> 00:01:46.389
The palms face upward
and remain open, and the

30
00:01:46.400 --> 00:01:47.979
child should not rush.

31
00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:51.259
Continue the exercise
for two to three minutes.

32
00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:52.759
We are not rushing.

33
00:01:53.580 --> 00:01:56.719
In this case, quality is
more important than speed.

34
00:01:57.560 --> 00:01:59.728
Pay attention to make
sure that the arms

35
00:01:59.740 --> 00:02:01.059
and legs move in sync.

36
00:03:09.700 --> 00:03:11.469
In this exercise,
we play snake.

37
00:03:12.020 --> 00:03:15.549
The child lies on their back
on a flat surface with the

38
00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:19.109
legs together and straight,
the arms pressed to the

39
00:03:19.120 --> 00:03:22.619
body, and the shoulder blades
pressed against the floor.

40
00:03:22.660 --> 00:03:26.169
With wave-like movements, the
child wriggles upward using

41
00:03:26.180 --> 00:03:30.479
the entire spine without
using the arms or legs.

42
00:03:30.540 --> 00:03:33.229
Do the exercise for
two to three minutes.

43
00:05:14.440 --> 00:05:17.309
In this exercise, the child
lies on their stomach with

44
00:05:17.320 --> 00:05:20.679
the head slightly raised and
the arms and legs extended.

45
00:05:21.180 --> 00:05:23.079
Make sure the head is raised.

46
00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:23.929
This is important.

47
00:05:24.370 --> 00:05:28.149
The child raises the left
arm and right leg diagonally

48
00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:30.899
with the gaze directed
toward the floor.

49
00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:33.699
Then the child switches
the arm and leg diagonally

50
00:05:33.710 --> 00:05:34.819
at the same time.

51
00:05:35.320 --> 00:05:37.609
Repeat the movements
very slowly for two

52
00:05:37.620 --> 00:05:38.519
to three minutes.

53
00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:42.389
The arms and legs stay engaged
the whole time and alternate

54
00:05:42.400 --> 00:05:44.179
one after the other.

55
00:05:44.190 --> 00:05:47.639
The exercise somewhat
resembles swimming in water.

56
00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:50.839
It is a fairly simple but
very effective exercise.

57
00:07:27.770 --> 00:07:30.829
For this exercise, you
will need any kind of ball.

58
00:07:30.870 --> 00:07:34.039
If you don't have a ball,
you can also use a toy, but

59
00:07:34.050 --> 00:07:35.439
a ball is more convenient.

60
00:07:35.760 --> 00:07:38.379
The child should press the
ball between their back

61
00:07:38.390 --> 00:07:42.169
and the wall and roll it up
and down and side to side.

62
00:07:42.210 --> 00:07:44.379
Imagine that a little
bear is scratching its

63
00:07:44.390 --> 00:07:45.389
back against a tree.

64
00:07:45.890 --> 00:07:48.389
Children usually really
love this exercise.

65
00:07:48.470 --> 00:07:50.249
Do it every day
for five minutes.

66
00:08:39.450 --> 00:08:42.589
We have now completed a block
of exercises for integrating

67
00:08:42.600 --> 00:08:43.749
the Galant reflex.

68
00:08:44.370 --> 00:08:47.209
You may notice different
reactions in your child.

69
00:08:47.330 --> 00:08:50.859
Some become calmer, while
others, on the contrary,

70
00:08:50.870 --> 00:08:52.199
become a little more active.

71
00:08:52.900 --> 00:08:53.729
This is normal.

72
00:08:54.490 --> 00:08:56.449
It is how the nervous
system adapts.

73
00:08:56.890 --> 00:08:59.839
It is important to do
these exercises regularly,

74
00:08:59.850 --> 00:09:01.029
but without overload.

75
00:09:01.490 --> 00:09:04.529
A little every day is better
than too much at once.

76
00:09:04.610 --> 00:09:07.179
Over time, you will notice
that it becomes easier

77
00:09:07.190 --> 00:09:10.059
for your child to sit
calmly and that overall

78
00:09:10.070 --> 00:09:11.429
tension decreases.

79
00:09:11.930 --> 00:09:12.749
See you soon.

